# SSeed

[![PyPI Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/sseed.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/sseed/)
[![CI Status](https://github.com/ethene/sseed/workflows/CI%2FCD%20Pipeline/badge.svg)](https://github.com/ethene/sseed/actions)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/sseed.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/sseed/)
[![Test Coverage](https://img.shields.io/badge/coverage-89.96%25-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/ethene/sseed)
[![Code Quality](https://img.shields.io/badge/pylint-9.86%2F10-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/ethene/sseed)

**Secure, offline BIP39/SLIP39 cryptocurrency seed management with multi-language support**

---

## ‚ú® Features

- üåç **Multi-Language BIP-39 Support** - Generate and restore mnemonics in 9 languages with automatic detection
- üîê **Generate secure BIP-39 mnemonics** with flexible word counts (12, 15, 18, 21, or 24 words) using cryptographically secure entropy
- üå± **Generate master seeds from mnemonics** using PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA512 per BIP-39 specification
- üéØ **BIP85 deterministic entropy derivation** - unlimited child wallets, passwords, and keys from single master
- üîÑ **Split secrets using SLIP-39** with flexible group/threshold configurations
- üîß **Reconstruct mnemonics from shards** with integrity validation
- üö´ **100% offline operation** - zero network calls, air-gapped security
- ‚ö° **Lightning fast** - sub-millisecond operations, <100MB memory usage
- üõ°Ô∏è **Secure memory handling** - automatic cleanup of sensitive data
- üß™ **Mathematical verification** - property-based testing with Hypothesis
- üéØ **Simple CLI interface** - intuitive commands, version info, scriptable automation
- üì¶ **Zero dependencies** - self-contained, easy deployment
- üåç **Cross-platform** - macOS, Linux, Windows compatibility

## üåç Multi-Language Support

SSeed supports all 9 official BIP-39 languages with automatic detection:

| Language | Code | Script | Example |
|----------|------|--------|---------|
| **English** | `en` | Latin | `abandon ability able...` |
| **Spanish** | `es` | Latin | `√°baco abdomen abedul...` |
| **French** | `fr` | Latin | `abaisser abandon abdiquer...` |
| **Italian** | `it` | Latin | `abaco abbaglio abbinare...` |
| **Portuguese** | `pt` | Latin | `abacate abalar abater...` |
| **Czech** | `cs` | Latin | `abdikace abeceda adresa...` |
| **Chinese (Simplified)** | `zh-cn` | Ideographic | `ÁöÑ ‰∏Ä ÊòØ Âú® ‰∏ç ‰∫Ü...` |
| **Chinese (Traditional)** | `zh-tw` | Ideographic | `ÁöÑ ‰∏Ä ÊòØ Âú® ‰∏ç ‰∫Ü...` |
| **Korean** | `ko` | Hangul | `Í∞ÄÍ≤© Í∞ÄÎÅî Í∞ÄÎÇú Í∞ÄÎä•...` |

### Language Features
- ‚úÖ **Automatic Detection** - Identifies mnemonic language with 95%+ accuracy
- ‚úÖ **Unicode Support** - Full support for international character sets
- ‚úÖ **Generate in Any Language** - Use `--language/-l` flag for generation
- ‚úÖ **Seamless Recovery** - Auto-detects language during restore operations
- ‚úÖ **100% Backward Compatible** - English remains default, existing code unchanged

## ‚ú® Key Features

- **üîê Secure Generation**: BIP-39 mnemonics with flexible word counts (12, 15, 18, 21, 24) using cryptographic entropy
- **üåç Multi-Language**: Generate and restore in 9 languages with auto-detection
- **üéØ BIP85 Deterministic Entropy**: Generate unlimited child wallets, passwords, and hex entropy from one master seed
- **üß© SLIP-39 Sharding**: Split mnemonics into threshold-based secret shares
- **üîÑ Perfect Recovery**: Reconstruct original mnemonics from sufficient shards
- **üå± Master Seed Generation**: BIP-39 compliant PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA512 seed derivation
- **üéØ BIP85 Deterministic Entropy**: Generate unlimited child wallets, passwords, and hex entropy from one master seed
- **üîç Entropy Display**: View underlying entropy alongside mnemonics for verification
- **‚ö° Cross-Tool Compatibility**: Full interoperability with official Trezor SLIP-39 CLI
- **üõ°Ô∏è Security First**: Memory cleanup, input validation, and comprehensive error handling
- **üìÅ Flexible I/O**: File operations, stdin/stdout, and batch processing support
- **üß™ Battle Tested**: 632 comprehensive tests with 95%+ code coverage

